Buffett Entitled to $200 Million If Lubrizol Backs Out of Deal

-- B y   D a n   K r a u t
-- 
2011-03-15T18:32:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-15/buffett-entitled-to-200-million-if-lubrizol-backs-out-of-deal.html
  Warren Buffett ’s Berkshire Hathaway
Inc. is entitled to a termination fee of $200 million from  Lubrizol Corp. (LZ)  if the lubricant maker backs out of the deal to
sell itself to the billionaire’s company.  Lubrizol disclosed the fee in a regulatory filing today
outlining its agreement to sell itself to Omaha, Nebraska-based
Berkshire for about $9 billion.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dan Kraut in New York at 
